The paper discusses the analysis of multi-layered social networks, which involves the study of complex relationships and interactions between nodes. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including social networks (cs.SOC), data structures (cs.DS), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and databases (cs.DB). However, since the paper focuses on the degree centrality measure, which is a common metric used in social network analysis, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of social informatics (cs.SI).
